# Upstream pin for the `gitea` service. THE pin consumed by compose lives in .env
# (GITEA_VERSION in .env.example) — keep it in sync with this file. Never "latest".
#
# IMAGE/VERSION/DIGEST below pin the stock upstream gitea/gitea SOURCE. Artea no
# longer runs that image unmodified: it builds a PATCHED image
# `ghcr.io/yisding/artea-gitea` = stock source at SOURCE_TAG + the gitea/patches/
# queue (currently the PKCE patch, ADR-0009), via gitea/build-image.sh and the
# `images` CI workflow. The patched image is opt-in — the chart default stays the
# stock image; `make dev` and production select the patched one (see ADR-0009).
# Keep IMAGE=gitea/gitea as the SOURCE pin (build base + clone tag), not the
# deployed image.

IMAGE=gitea/gitea
VERSION=1.26.2
# multi-arch manifest list digest for gitea/gitea:1.26.2 (Docker Hub, 2026-05-20)
DIGEST=sha256:7d13848af12645600a5f9d93ee2560daa9c6fa6b5b859b7bff3a5e1c0b661031
# git tag the runtime overlay (app.ini keys, custom/templates) AND the patched
# image source build (gitea/build-image.sh) are verified against
SOURCE_TAG=v1.26.2

# Bump procedure (also re-run after any overlay change):
# 1. Pick the new stable tag from https://github.com/go-gitea/gitea/releases
#    (and its digest from Docker Hub). Update VERSION/DIGEST/SOURCE_TAG here and
#    GITEA_VERSION in .env / .env.example.
# 2. Re-verify the template overlay against upstream template changes — every file
#    under gitea/custom/templates/ shadows an upstream file wholesale, so upstream
#    fixes there do NOT take effect until re-merged:
#      for f in base/head_navbar.tmpl home.tmpl; do
#        diff <(curl -sf https://raw.githubusercontent.com/go-gitea/gitea/<NEW_TAG>/templates/$f) \
#             <(curl -sf https://raw.githubusercontent.com/go-gitea/gitea/<OLD_TAG>/templates/$f)
#      done
#    If upstream changed a shadowed file, re-copy it and re-apply the marked
#    "ARTEA:" edits (they are listed at the top of each override).
# 3. Re-verify app.ini keys against the new tag's custom/conf/app.example.ini
#    (breaking config changes are listed in the upstream release notes).
# 4. The gitea/patches/ queue is non-empty (PKCE patch, ADR-0009): after bumping
#    SOURCE_TAG, run `gitea/patches/apply-patches.sh --check <checkout>` against a
#    checkout of the new tag, re-verify the queue applies AND the package
#    compiles, rebase any failing patch (patches/README.md), then rebuild the
#    patched image with gitea/build-image.sh.
# 5. `make up` — watch the gitea container log for config deprecation warnings.
# 6. `make e2e` — the S1-S12 scenarios are the acceptance gate.
